Karıncalı
Karıncalı is a town in Orhaneli district of Bursa Province, Turkey. It is situated to the north of Orhaneli creek at . The distance to Orhaneli is . The population of the town is 2087 as of 2011. Although the present name of the town Karıncalı means "with ant" the original name "Karın" refers to maternal brothers. The settlement was founded by 10 families of Turkmen Kayı tribe after Orhan of Ottoman Empire captured Orhaneli in early 14th century. In 1994, the settlement was declared a seat of township .
